text: Boina may refer to: * It is the Spanish, Portuguese, Galician and Catalan word for beret. * Dabbahu Volcano, also known as Boina, is a volcano in Ethiopia * Boina, a former kingdom in Madagascar * Boina, a village in Dalboșeț Commune, Caraș-Severin County, Romania * Taxonomic synonym for Boinae, a subfamily of boid snakes.
title: Boina
